00:01:12.840 --> 00:01:19.840
purpose of evaluating a mean change in the baseline symptoms with reduction in some biomarkers,

00:01:19.840 --> 00:01:26.260
including serone triptase, bone marrow muscle burden, and a KIT reduction.

00:01:27.280 --> 00:01:35.860
The primary point for the summit was met at 24 weeks, where there is a significant reduction

00:01:35.860 --> 00:01:43.240
in the symptom score, where the symptom score that were worse eventually get better after 24

00:01:43.240 --> 00:01:49.260
weeks of current treatment with pesuclastinib treatment. And this is significant with the

00:01:49.260 --> 00:01:57.060
p-value that is demonstrated over here. When the results were evaluated according to different

00:01:57.260 --> 00:02:03.040
group of symptoms, all of the symptoms in general got benefit with the addition of pesuclastinib,

00:02:03.040 --> 00:02:08.040
including neurocognitive symptoms, skin, and constitutional symptoms such as fatigue.

00:02:10.400 --> 00:02:16.080
And I just mentioned one slide of the bone marrow muscle burden that notably achieved

00:02:16.080 --> 00:02:20.720
significant reduction. In fact, it was one of the reasons for presentation at us regarding

00:02:20.720 --> 00:02:26.520
the pathological response in pesuclastinib for those patients treated with indolent systemic

00:02:26.520 --> 00:02:27.240
mastocytosis.

00:02:27.240 --> 00:02:35.660
The safety profile was relatively remarkable towards no major significant side effects,

00:02:35.660 --> 00:02:41.320
with exception of LFT elevations that in a number of cases were transient and returning

00:02:41.320 --> 00:02:48.260
to the baseline after decreasing the dose or holding the medication temporarily.

00:02:48.260 --> 00:02:55.540
